{# Kubernetes Job manifest for one nnUNetv2 fold training run.
   Rendered by modelfactory.jobs.nnunet.submit().

   Kueue contract (v0.15+):
     - label `kueue.x-k8s.io/queue-name`: LABEL not annotation (annotation form removed)
     - label `kueue.x-k8s.io/priority-class` for preemption ordering

   GPU contract — MIG-UUID pinning (post-2026-05-20):
     - The leased MIG UUID is baked into env_pairs as NVIDIA_VISIBLE_DEVICES
       *before* this template is rendered (modelfactory.jobs.nnunet._lease_mig_uuid).
     - runtimeClassName: nvidia-legacy honours the env value; the default
       `nvidia` runtime would override it via CDI annotations (CLAUDE.md
       non-negotiable #2 + memory `gpu_runtime_class_lesson.md`).
     - No `nvidia.com/gpu` resource request: the device plugin advertises
       both MIG slices on GPUs 3-7 AND the whole un-MIG'd cards (GPUs 0/1/2),
       so requesting it can leak training to GPU 0 (reserved for the QA viewer)
       or GPUs 1/2 (vLLM medgemma). The lease ConfigMap + the 10-slice safe
       pool are the only allocators.

   Pod contract:
     - shm-size: emptyDir of medium: Memory at /dev/shm (Job spec equivalent of --shm-size)

   Inputs:
     args: list[str]        positional + flag args for nnUNetv2_train
     env_pairs: list[dict]  [{name, value | valueFrom}, ...] — includes
                            NVIDIA_VISIBLE_DEVICES={leased MIG UUID}
#}
apiVersion: batch/v1
kind: Job
metadata:
  name: {{ job_name }}
  namespace: {{ namespace }}
  labels:
    app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: modelfactory
    factory.io/dataset: {{ dataset | replace('_', '-') | lower }}
    factory.io/configuration: {{ configuration }}
    factory.io/fold: "{{ fold }}"
    kueue.x-k8s.io/queue-name: {{ queue_name }}
    kueue.x-k8s.io/priority-class: {{ priority_class }}
spec:
  backoffLimit: 0
  ttlSecondsAfterFinished: 604800
  parallelism: 1
  completions: 1
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: modelfactory
        factory.io/dataset: {{ dataset | replace('_', '-') | lower }}
        factory.io/configuration: {{ configuration }}
        factory.io/fold: "{{ fold }}"
    spec:
      restartPolicy: Never
      {{ runtime_class_line }}
      nodeSelector: {{ node_selector | tojson }}
      containers:
      - name: trainer
        image: {{ image }}
        imagePullPolicy: IfNotPresent
        # bash -c wrapper: rsync the dataset's preprocessed/ dir from NFS into
        # the /factory-ram tmpfs (read-hot path lives in RAM, ~30-60 s for the
        # 65-92 GiB brain-MR datasets), then exec nnUNetv2_train with the
        # original positional args. The .stage_complete sentinel makes the
        # rsync idempotent so a restart-from-checkpoint doesn't re-pay it.
        # Script + args are pre-built in Python (gotcha #5: no Jinja blocks here).
        command: {{ command | tojson }}
        args: {{ args | tojson }}
        env: {{ env_pairs | tojson }}
        resources:
          requests:
            cpu: "{{ cpu_request }}"
            memory: "{{ memory_request }}"
          limits:
            cpu: "{{ cpu_limit }}"
            memory: "{{ memory_limit }}"
            {{ gpu_limit_line }}
        volumeMounts:
        - { name: factory-data, mountPath: /factory }
        - { name: dshm,         mountPath: /dev/shm }
        - { name: factory-ram,  mountPath: /factory-ram }
      volumes:
      - name: factory-data
        persistentVolumeClaim: { claimName: factory-data-pvc }
      - name: dshm
        emptyDir: { medium: Memory, sizeLimit: "{{ shm_size }}" }
      - name: factory-ram
        emptyDir: { medium: Memory, sizeLimit: "{{ ram_stage_size }}" }
